cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the problem of dynamic spatial graph construction in graph neural networks for time series data. It proposes a novel approach using spatial and temporal tensor graphs and explores their entangled correlations using Projected Entangled Pair States (PEPS) to optimize the two graphs. This work involves machine learning (ML) techniques, specifically graph neural networks, and optimization methods, which are commonly found in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper uses traffic datasets, which are often analyzed using computer vision (CV) and signal processing techniques, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.SI (Signal Processing) likely sub-categories as well.
